data.content:
## What Changed

`Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` 10.0 upgrades to **Microsoft.OpenApi v2**, which targets **OpenAPI 3.1**. Here are the breaking changes affecting your code:

| .NET 9 (OpenApi v1) | .NET 10 (OpenApi v2) | Why |
|---|---|---|
| `OpenApiString`, `OpenApiInteger`, etc. | `JsonNode` (`System.Text.Json.Nodes`) | `IOpenApiAny` types were removed |
| `schema.Nullable = true/false` | `schema.Type \|= JsonSchemaType.Null` | OpenAPI 3.1 uses type arrays for nullability |
| `new OpenApiSecurityScheme { Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = …, Id = … } }` | `new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("id")` | Dedicated reference subclasses replace the generic pattern |

## Fixed Code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;          // replaces Microsoft.OpenApi.Any
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References; // new reference types

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        // OpenApiString is gone — use JsonNode instead
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    // Use the dedicated reference class instead of OpenApiSecurityScheme + OpenApiReference
    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
            {
                // Nullable property is removed in OpenAPI 3.1;
                // nullability is expressed via the type keyword
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
            }
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

### Summary of changes

1. **`using` directives** — drop `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any`, add `System.Text.Json.Nodes` and `Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References`.
2. **`new OpenApiString("1.0")`** → **`JsonValue.Create("1.0")`** — all `IOpenApiAny` primitives are replaced by `JsonNode`.
3. **Security scheme reference** — replace the `OpenApiSecurityScheme` + `OpenApiReference` combo with **`new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2")`**.
4. **`Nullable = false`** → **`Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null`** — OpenAPI 3.1 models nullability as a type flag, not a boolean.
